parameters:
Sister Eleo: I'm sorry for going to the Roxos Fortress
without telling you it was dangerous.
Sister Sophia: Hehe, it's okay because you're safe.

Sister Eleo: And I also contacted the Adventurer's Guild
without permission...

Sister Sophia: Isn't it unfair? Like, there was pressure
from the nobles in the campus.

Sister Eleo: You know everything, don't you? Is that also
the result of your information gathering at the tavern?
Sister Sophia: Hehe, that's a secret...

Sister Eleo: Thank you all so much for saving my life. I'm
grateful.

Sister Eleo: If you don't mind, please come and rest your
weary travels in Irini Village.

Mage Relm: We don't have time for that! We need to follow
the dragon's footsteps!
Sister Sophia: Oh, speaking of that, about that matter--

Campus Guard: Ladies! Have you seen any suspicious
individuals?

Clea: There is a kidnapper at Fort Roxos. They have been
tied up, so please come and collect them.
Campus Guard: What?! Leave that to us!

Campus Guard: Have you seen any other suspicious
individuals?

Campus Guard: Thank you for your cooperation. We will head
to Fort Roxos together to search for the Phantom Thief
Perno!

Sister Sophia: It's a notorious thief causing a commotion
in the empire. According to rumors, they are said to be a
contract holder with demons.

Mage Relm: That's not possible! There's absolutely no way
to make a contract with demons.

Mage Relm: The 65 demons sealed by the ancestor of the
mages, Subma, were defeated by the 7 demon slaying heroes...
But in the first place, demons...
Thief Nora: Um, excuse me, may I ask something?
Mage Relm: We're in the middle of something important!

Thief Nora: U-Um, excuse me, but I'm curious about the
person behind us.

Mysterious Woman: Oh, you have a keen sense to notice me...
But more importantly, do you have good ears and nose?

Mysterious Woman: Do you know about the Phantom Thief
Perno?

Phantom Thief Perno: Hehe, well then, goodbye Thanks to
you, I was able to escape from the guards, so I appreciate
it.
